{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/vstack\/geometrygroup()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack\/geometryGroup()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from its parent view.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed down to each subview."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ItemView"},{"type":"text","text":" may be added and removed at different times the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applied."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parent view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"title":"geometryGroup()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPA